I'm always looking for something new, but to be honest Korean BBQ would not have been in my top choices to try.
This place really changed my mind and I learned a little about the culture in the process.
Korean BBQ is not like American BBQ.
The cooking is done at your table over gas grills.
Some places will bring a portable gas grill  to your table, this place has the grills built into the tables ( learned this from my server).
The menu was good because they had pictures of the dishes  so you could see what you're ordering.
We asked the server about something we'd seen on the front window called Mondu as an appetizer.
It's kind of like a chinese pot sticker, but I like these much better.
They come on a sizzling platter.
When it came to the main dish we tried the Kal Bi.
It's a thin sliced marinated beef rib - in my opinion just short of heaven.
Your meal comes with a variety of vegetable side dishes served in small bowls for all to share.
I had to ask what some of them were as I couldn't tell the difference between zucchini and cucumber, as well as some that were made from turnip (real good even though I'd have thought I wouldn't like it) My favorite was the spinach (again, who knew?
), but they vary from day to day - just be aware of the variety.
They have romaine lettuce leaves served with to use as a wrap, but I prefer just to dig into the meat and sides separately.
I had a Korean beer (Hite?
) and it was tasty.
I also tried some hot tea, which was different.
It's not like chinese tea - it has more of a wheaty flavor that I have come to love.
Food - Great; Service - Great; and Karaoke if you want to sing afterwards.
It's a great experience!

